A safe LibreOffice-compatible formula for `B9:B100` is:
`=IF(A9="","",IF(A9>MAX($C$6:$V$6),"",COUNTIF($C$6:$V$6,"<"&A9)+1))`

This:
- leaves blank if A cell is blank,
- leaves blank for apple indices beyond total apples (rows 101+ not present, but rows 93:100 have A indices >92 and should stay blank),
